Caribou Habitat class

Source: R/AAAClassDefinitions.R
CaribouHabitat-class.Rd

An object containing data and results for the caribou habitat resource selection function

Slots

landCover

SpatRaster with land cover classified into resource types. See resTypeCode for a legend.

esker

SpatRaster of esker density in m^2 per hectare.

natDist

SpatRaster of natural disturbance.

anthroDist

SpatRaster of anthropogenic disturbances.

linFeat

SpatRaster of linear feature density in m^2 per hectare.

projectPoly

Sf object with polygon of project boundary.

processedData

SpatRaster with named layers for each input variable used in the RSF

habitatUse

SpatRaster with named layers for each season

attributes

A list of arguments from the caribouHabtat call.

See also

See caribouHabitat() for options when creating a CaribouHabitat object.

Caribou habitat functions: calcBinaryUse(), caribouHabitat(), coefTableHR, coefTableStd, fnlcToResType, loadSpatialInputs(), plcToResType, rasterizeLineDensity(), reclassPLC(), resTypeCode, results(), rfuToResType, threshTable, updateCaribou()
